{
  "texts": [
    "This results in highly biased datasets and makes it difficult to learn to recognize rare species, having a serious impact on the performance of classifiers.",
    "Furthermore, with highly unbalanced datasets the overall classification accuracy (e.g.",
    "percentage of images that were correctly classified) provides little information about the classes with a small number of samples which may bias the evaluation of the goodness of the classification methods. 3.",
    "Visual differences between certain classes are small.",
    "Certain plankton species, especially those that are taxonomically close to each other and/or have reduced size, resemble each other visually, which renders the recognition task a fine-grained classification problem."
  ]
}